                    <subsection>
                        <title>Tasks</title>
                        <ol>
                            <li>
                                <p> Ask your student to open the cover of the BrailleNote</p>
                            
                            <ul>
                                <li>
                                    <p> The cover should open away from the BrailleNote user</p>
                                </li>
                                <li>
                                    <p> If the BrailleNote is positioned correctly, your student will recognize six Braille writer keys and a spacebar which are similar to that of a Perkins Braille writer</p>
                                </li>
                            </ul></li>
                            <li>
                                <p> Assist your student in locating the on off switch located under the velcro flap toward the back of the left panel of the BrailleNote</p>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <p> Before turning the BrailleNote on </p>
                            
                            <ul>
                                <li>
                                    <p> Explain that when the rocker switch is indented toward the user, the BrailleNote is on </p>
                                </li>
                                <li>
                                    <p> When the on off switch is indented away from the user, the BrailleNote is of</p>
                                </li>
