                <section>
                    <title> Email</title>
                    <p>Skills Addressed in this Lesson:</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>
                            <p> Connect to a server.</p>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <p> Read new mail messages.</p>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <p> Put unwanted messages in trash folder.</p>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <p> Complete and understand fields required for creating an e-mail message.</p>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <p> Write a simple e-mail message.</p>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <p> Edit e-mail message as needed.</p>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <p> Send e-mail message when ready.</p>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <p> Create a new e-mail folder.</p>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <p> Exit e-mail.</p>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <p> Send messages and empty trash as required.</p>
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                    <subsection>
                        <title>Tasks</title>
                        <p>This lesson assumes that your student has an up and running e-mail account and the service has already been added to the BrailleNote. This lesson assumes that the teacher is familiar with hooking the BrailleNote to the Internet and that this has been previously set up.</p>
                        <ol>
                            <li>
                                <p> From the Main Menu, open email application  <em>letter e</em></p>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <p> When in Keymail, cycle menu options:  <em>space</em></p>
                            
                            <ul>
                                <li>
                                    <p> write an e-mail</p>
                                </li>
                                <li>
                                    <p> read e-mail</p>
                                </li>
                                <li>
                                    <p> connect to a service</p>
                                </li>
                                <li>
                                    <p> setup options</p>
                                </li>
                            </ul></li>
                            <li>
                                <p> At the connect to a service prompt, when service name is displayed  <em>enter</em></p>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <p> Access "read email'' option  <em>space</em> or <em>advance thumb-key</em></p>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <p> Toggle options to access the inbox  <em>space, enter</em></p>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <p> At the cue to check for new messages  <em>enter</em></p>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <p> When in an e-mail message:</p>
                           
                            <ul>
                                <li>
                                    <p> move from field to field  <em>space</em></p>
                                </li>
                                <li>
                                    <p> Move back by field  <em>Backspace will move back by field</em></p>
                                
                                <ul>
                                    <li>
                                        <p> subject</p>
                                    </li>
                                    <li>
                                        <p> date</p>
                                    </li>
                                    <li>
                                        <p> e-mail address</p>
                                    </li>
                                    <li>
                                        <p> etc</p>
                                    </li>
                                </ul></li>
                            </ul></li>
                            <li>
                                <p> To move to the next e-mail message <em>space + dots56</em></p>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <p> Move to previous email <em>space + dots23</em></p>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <p> To put an unwanted message in the trash  <em>space + dots2356</em></p>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <p> To read e-mail message  <em>enter</em></p>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <p> Read the e-mail message with the following commands:</p>
                           
                            <ul>
                                <li>
                                    <p> Go forward reading automatically <em>space + g</em></p>
                                </li>
                                <li>
                                    <p> To move back a character  <em>space + dot3</em></p>
                                </li>
                                <li>
                                    <p> To read the current character  <em>space + dots36</em></p>
                                </li>
                                <li>
                                    <p> To move forward by character <em>space + dot6</em></p>
                                </li>
                                <li>
                                    <p> To move to the top of the message  <em>space + dots123</em></p>
                                </li>
                                <li>
                                    <p> Move to the end of message  <em>space + dots456</em></p>
                                </li>
                                <li>
                                    <p> Move back a word <em>space + dot2</em></p>
                                </li>
                                <li>
                                    <p> Read current word  <em>space + dots25</em></p>
                                </li>
                                <li>
                                    <p> Read forward by word  <em>space + dot5</em></p>
                                </li>
                                <li>
                                    <p> Read back a sentence  <em>space + dot1</em></p>
                                </li>
                                <li>
                                    <p> Read the current sentence  <em>space + dots14</em></p>
                                </li>
                                <li>
                                    <p> Read forward by sentence  <em>space + dot4</em></p>
                                </li>
                                <li>
                                    <p> To read back by paragraph  <em>space + dots23</em></p>
                                </li>
                                <li>
                                    <p> To read the current paragraph  <em>space + dots2356</em></p>
                                </li>
                                <li>
                                    <p> To read forward by paragraph  <em>space + dots56</em></p>
                                </li>
                                <li>
                                    <p> Move Back or Forward one display length  <em>advance thumb-key</em> or <em>back thumb-key</em></p>
                                </li>
                                <li>
                                    <p> Start braille display moving automatically  <em> space + dots23456 </em></p>
                                
                                <ul>
                                    <li>
                                        <p> Control the speed of braille display <em>previous thumb-key, next thumb-key</em></p>
                                    </li>
                                    <li>
                                        <p> Stop the display from automatically moving <em>previous thumb-key + next thumb-key</em></p>
                                    </li>
                                </ul></li>
                            </ul></li>
                            <li>
                                <p> When your student has finished reading the e-mail message, he or she may press space with e.  "Move this e-mail to which folder?" will be the prompt.</p>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <p> To create a new e-mail folder from here, your student may type the name he or she wishes to use and press enter.  Respond with a y for yes at the "create a new folder" prompt.  The e-mail can then be moved to this folder.</p>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <p> To select an existing folder to move the e-mail to, use space or the advance thumb-key to locate the desired folder.  Press enter to move the e-mail to the folder.</p>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <p> When e-mail has been read, use space with e to return to the keymail menu options menu.  Locate "write an e-mail" and press enter.</p>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <p> Your student will first need to fill out the Send To field.  The e-mail address of the person who you wish to e-mail will go here.  Computer Braille is required for e-mail addresses.  Do not use Braille contractions.  For the at sign, use space with u followed by the dot4. To move to the next field, use the advance thumb-key. A dot is written with dots4 6.</p>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <p> If you wish to e-mail your message to someone else, fill out the "also send to" field with the e-mail address of another person.  Use the advance thumb-key to move to the next field.</p>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <p> The "blind copy field" can also be filled out with an e-mail address.</p>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <p> This copy will go to the recipient without anyone but you and the recipient knowing about it.  Explain this to your student and help them to use and understand the fields.</p>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <p> The "attach a file" field is for attaching a file from the BrailleNote to an e-mail message that can then be opened and read by the recipient.</p>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <p> Your student may write a subject in the subject field.  The subject can be one or two words that will summarize the content of the e-mail message.</p>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <p> In the message area, write a simple e-mail message.  Edit the message as you wish before sending it.  A review of some editing commands is given below.</p>
                            
                            <ol>
                                <li>
                                    <p> Delete to end of sentence by using backspace with dots1 and 4.</p>
                                </li>
                                <li>
                                    <p> To delete the word under the cursor, use backspace with dots2 and 5.</p>
                                </li>
                                <li>
                                    <p> Use backspace with dot2 to delete the word before the cursor.</p>
                                </li>
                                <li>
                                    <p> To delete to the end of the paragraph, press backspace with dots2 3 5 6.</p>
                                </li>
                                <li>
                                    <p> Use dots4 5 6 with backspace to delete from the cursor to the end of the message.</p>
                                </li>
                                <li>
                                    <p> Use the cursor keys and backspace to make corrections and insertions.</p>
                                </li>
                            </ol></li>
                            <li>
                                <p> When you and your student are satisfied with the message, use e with space to begin the process of sending an e-mail.  Press y when asked if you are ready to send the message.</p>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <p> When asked if you wish to save a copy, press n for no.  If you key in y for yes, you will be prompted to save the e-mail in the desired folder of your student's choice.</p>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <p> To exit Keymail, press space with e.  To send the mail your student wrote, he or she should press e with space and y for yes when prompted to do so.  Remember, if you write an e-mail when your BrailleNote is not connected to the internet, you will not be able to send e-mail messages immediately.  Your mail will be sent the next time that you connect to the internet.</p>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <p> You and your student will also be prompted as to whether or not the e-mail in the trash folder should be emptied.  Key in a y for yes if you would like the trash to be emptied.</p>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <p> At this point you and your student should be placed back at the Main Menu.  As always, turn the BrailleNote off when work tasks are completed.</p>
                            </li>
                        </ol>
                    </subsection>
                    <subsection>
                        <title>Quiz</title>
                        <ol>
