                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <p> "Entry list for address list" is what will be displayed and spoken.</p>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <p> Use "space or backspace" or "previous or advance" to move from field to field.  Think of a friend or family member.  Add an address to the address book.</p>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <p> If you know the information for the fields, enter it.  If you are instructed to do so, use computer Braille.  Computer Braille uses no contractions.  The at symbol is entered by using space with dots1 3 6 followed by dot4. Address fields include the following:</p>
                            
