                <section>
                    <title>Overview of the BrailleNote Touch</title>
                    <p>The BrailleNote Touch is a tablet with a Braille display. It comes in a protective carrying case that includes a Perkins-style keyboard.</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>
                            <p> The keyboard</p>
                        </li>
                        <ul>
                            <li>
                                <p> Six keys for Brailling</p>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <p> Enter key on the right</p>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <p> Backspace key on the left</p>
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                        <li>
                            <p> The front edge of the tablet contains four thumb keys. From left to right:</p>
                        </li>
                        <ul>
                            <li>
                                <p> Previous</p>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <p> Pan left</p>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <p> Pan right</p>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <p> Next</p>
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                        <li>
                            <p> In the middle of the front edge are three additional keys. From left to right:</p>
